<td valign="top" class="postbody">
<hr />
Wow, I'd like to read that book, or pamphlet lol. The Westin is actually supposed to be haunted. I think it's a Hilton now... or maybe it's not... well anyway, one of them is supposed to be haunted with a lady in a green dress. I forget why she's supposed to be haunting the place, but a lot of people claim to have seen her.
<br />

<br />
The subway... yeah, it's got a great history to it. I just don't know enough of it by memory to tell any of it. They give tours too. You just have to sign up and be prepared to wait a year before going thru because it's always full. But basically, the guy that became Mayor at that time decided to build this subway and bind two sides of the city together. Everyone loved the idea and that's how he got into office. But after they started, the city ran out of money half way thru the project, and it was abandoned, never to be finished. However lately they've been talking of finishing it and binding those areas, because they still haven't gotten their public transportation, the Metro buses, to take people from the east side to the west side. And that's where the subway will go. But the final word hasn't been put out yet, and I found that out about a year ago.
<br />

<br />
But people claim the tunnel that is finished is haunted, and I don't think it is. It's just kind of a ghost-subway because it was never finished and almost never talked about by anyone in this city because we all grew up with it. We don't think of it as odd because it's always been there, and you can visibly see it on the north bound side of I-75 about 5-7 miles outside of downtown. There's also a tiny bit that was finished along the northbound side of I-71. But I had traveled that highway for a year before someone told me about it and I finally seen it because there isn't enough to actually catch your attention. But it's pretty cool when you hear the history to it and realize that at one time it was all the city talked about. And now, nothing.
<br />

<br />
And if you ever come back this way, let me know and we'll go out hunting somewhere.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: And oh yeah, Over The Rhine SUCKS ASS CRACKS. That's the ugly, unwanted step child of Cincinnati.</td>
</tr>
